## Deploy with Docker

```bash
docker build -t {{PACKAGE_NAME}} .
docker run -p 3000:3000 --env-file .env {{PACKAGE_NAME}}
# the server now speaks Streamable HTTP at http://localhost:3000/mcp
```

## Configuration

Configuration is read from the environment (see `.env.example`):

| Variable | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `MCPGEN_API_BASE_URL` | Upstream API base URL (default `{{API_BASE_URL}}`). |
| `MCPGEN_TRANSPORT` | `stdio` (local) or `http` (Streamable HTTP). |
| `MCPGEN_HTTP_PORT` | Port for the http transport (default `3000`). |

Credentials are read from the environment and never hardcoded — see
`.env.example` and `SECURITY.md`.

## Security

Read **`SECURITY.md`** before deploying. mcpgen-generated handlers are a starting
point and must be reviewed by an operator.
